the [[American Athletic Conference]].\n\n==Previous season==\nThe [[2019-20 Wichita State Shockers men's basketball team|Shockers]] finished the [[2019\u201320 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2019\u201320 season]] 23-8, 11-7 in [[2019\u201320 American Athletic Conference men's basketball season|AAC play]] and finished in fourth place. They entered as the No. 4 seed in the [[2020 American Athletic Conference Men's Basketball Tournament|AAC Tournament]], which was ultimately cancelled due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].\n\n== Offseason ==\n\n=== Departures ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n!Name \n!Number\n!Pos.\n!Height \n!Weight \n!Year\n!Hometown\n!Reason\n|-\n| Jamarius Burton\n| 2\n| G\n| 6'3\"\n| 200\n| {{sort|2|Sophomore}}\n| [[Charlotte, North Carolina]]\n| Transferred\n|-\n| DeAntoni Gordon\n| 3\n| F\n| 6'7\"\n| 210\n| {{sort|1|Freshman}}\n| [[Mobile, Alabama]]\n| Transferred\n|-\n| Erik Stevenson\n| 10\n| G\n| 6'3\"\n| 198\n| {{sort|2|Sophomore}}\n| [[Lacey, Washington]]\n| Transferred\n|-\n| Noah Fernandes\n| 11\n| G\n| 5'11\"\n| 172\n| {{sort|1|Freshman}}\n| [[Mattapoisett, Massachusetts]]\n| Transferred\n|-\n| Jaime Echenique\n| 21\n| C\n| 6'11\"\n| 258\n| {{sort|4|Senior}}\n| [[Barranquilla|Barranquilla, Colombia]]\n| Graduated\n|-\n| Morris Udeze\n| 24\n| C\n| 6'8\"\n| 240\n| {{sort|2|Sophomore}}\n| [[Houston|Houston, Texas]]\n| Transferred\n|-\n| Tate Busse\n| 32\n| G\n| 6'2\"\n| 185\n| {{sort|1|Freshman}}\n| [[St. Francis, Kansas]]\n| Walk-on; transferred\n|-\n| Asbj\u00f8rn Midtgaard\n| 33\n| C\n| 7'0\"\n| 267\n| {{sort|3|Junior}}\n| [[Helsing\u00f8r|Helsing\u00f8r, Denmark]]\n| Transferred\n|-\n| Grant Sherfield\n| 52\n| G\n| 6'2\"\n| 189\n| {{sort|1|Freshman}}\n| [[Wichita, Kansas]]\n| Transferred\n|-\n|}\n\n=== 2020 recruiting class ===\n{{College Athlete Recruit Start|40=no|collapse=no|year=2020}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry\n| recruit  = Ricky Council IV\n| position = G\n| hometown